mibimaGroupConfigTable.name: mibimaGroupConfigTable
mibimaGroupConfigTable.description: A list of mibimaGroupConfig profile entries.

mibimaGroupConfigEntry.name: mibimaGroupConfigEntry
mibimaGroupConfigEntry.description: A mibimaGroupConfig entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibimaGroupConfig profile.

imaGroupConfig_Name.name: imaGroupConfig_Name
imaGroupConfig_Name.description: Name of IMA Group Config profile.

imaGroupConfig_Active.name: imaGroupConfig_Active
imaGroupConfig_Active.description: TRUE if the line is enabled, otherwise FALSE.

imaGroupConfig_NailedGroup.name: imaGroupConfig_NailedGroup
imaGroupConfig_NailedGroup.description: The nailed group to which this IMA group belongs to

imaGroupConfig_GroupSymmetryMode.name: imaGroupConfig_GroupSymmetryMode
imaGroupConfig_GroupSymmetryMode.description: Symmetry mode of group to which this link belongs to

imaGroupConfig_DoVersionFallback.name: imaGroupConfig_DoVersionFallback
imaGroupConfig_DoVersionFallback.description: Automatically fall back to v 1.0 if FE is detected to be v 1.0, otherwise move to configAborted state

imaGroupConfig_IgnoreLineup.name: imaGroupConfig_IgnoreLineup
imaGroupConfig_IgnoreLineup.description: Ignore line up value for this IMA Group.

imaGroupConfig_Lasr.name: imaGroupConfig_Lasr
imaGroupConfig_Lasr.description: enable/disable LASR (Link addition and slow recovery) procedures

imaGroupConfig_TxMinNumLinks.name: imaGroupConfig_TxMinNumLinks
imaGroupConfig_TxMinNumLinks.description: Minimum Number of Tx Links to be active for group to remain in operational state

imaGroupConfig_RxMinNumLinks.name: imaGroupConfig_RxMinNumLinks
imaGroupConfig_RxMinNumLinks.description: Minimum Number of Rx Links to be active for group to remain in operational state

imaGroupConfig_DiffDelayMax.name: imaGroupConfig_DiffDelayMax
imaGroupConfig_DiffDelayMax.description: Maximum differential delay of group in msec

imaGroupConfig_CheckFarEndImaId.name: imaGroupConfig_CheckFarEndImaId
imaGroupConfig_CheckFarEndImaId.description: check/compare the expected-far-end-ima-id with the far-end IMA ID during group start up

imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndImaId.name: imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndImaId
imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndImaId.description: if check-far-end-ima-id set to yes, then the far-end IMA ID is compared against this number during group startup, GSM moves to ConfigAborted if it does not match

imaGroupConfig_FarEndCheckFrameLength.name: imaGroupConfig_FarEndCheckFrameLength
imaGroupConfig_FarEndCheckFrameLength.description: check/compare the Expected frame length with the far-end frame length during group start up

imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndFrameLength.name: imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndFrameLength
imaGroupConfig_ExpectedFarEndFrameLength.description: If far-end-check-frame-length is set to yes, then the far-end frame length is compared against this number during group startup, GSM moves to ConfigAborted, if it does not match.

imaGroupConfig_AtmIfDelay.name: imaGroupConfig_AtmIfDelay
imaGroupConfig_AtmIfDelay.description: minimum time (in seconds) between the subsequent ATM layer (ie IDCR changes) indications

imaGroupConfig_TppTestLink.name: imaGroupConfig_TppTestLink
imaGroupConfig_TppTestLink.description: Designate a link index as the test link for use in the Test Pattern Procedure.

imaGroupConfig_TppTestPattern.name: imaGroupConfig_TppTestPattern
imaGroupConfig_TppTestPattern.description: The test pattern transmitted in the ICP cell (octet 17) on the link during the IMA Test Pattern Procedure.

imaGroupConfig_TppState.name: imaGroupConfig_TppState
imaGroupConfig_TppState.description: Enable or disable the Test Pattern Procedure.

imaGroupConfig_VpSwitchingVpi.name: imaGroupConfig_VpSwitchingVpi
imaGroupConfig_VpSwitchingVpi.description: The Vpi to be used for the VP switching. Rest of the valid VPIs in valid vpi-vci-range will be used for the VC switching. Changes in this range will take effect immediately. THE USER SHOULD BE VERY CAREFUL WHILE CHANGING THIS VALUE BECAUSE ALL CONNECTIONS ON THE LIM WHERE THIS PORT BELONGS WILL BE DROPPED IN ORDER TO MAKE THIS NEW VALUE EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY.
